from PIL import Image
import numpy as np
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
from scipy.linalg import svd
from skimage.metrics import peak_signal_noise_ratio as psnr, structural_similarity as ssim

#  
image_path = '/Users/fanyi/Downloads/IMG_1459.JPG'

#  
image = Image.open(image_path).convert('L')
image_array = np.array(image) / 255.0

#  SVD 
U, S, Vt = svd(image_array, full_matrices=False)
m, n = image_array.shape

#   k 
k_values = [5, 10, 20, 50, 100, 150, 200]
psnr_values = []
ssim_values = []
compression_ratios = []

#   k 
for k in k_values:
    U_k = U[:, :k]
    S_k = np.diag(S[:k])
    Vt_k = Vt[:k, :]
    compressed = np.clip(U_k @ S_k @ Vt_k, 0, 1)

    psnr_values.append(psnr(image_array, compressed, data_range=1))
    ssim_values.append(ssim(image_array, compressed, data_range=1))
    compression_ratios.append((k * (m + n + 1)) / (m * n) * 100)

#  
plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
plt.plot(k_values, psnr_values, 'o-', label='PSNR (dB)')
plt.plot(k_values, ssim_values, 's-', label='SSIM')
plt.plot(k_values, compression_ratios, '^-', label='Compression Ratio (%)')
plt.xlabel('Rank (k)')
plt.ylabel('Metric Value')
plt.title('SVD Compression: PSNR, SSIM & Compression Ratio vs. Rank (k)')
plt.legend()
plt.grid(True)
plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()

# Choose rank-k for approximation (e.g., k=50)
k = 50

# Truncate singular values
U_k = U[:, :k]
S_k = np.diag(S[:k])
Vt_k = Vt[:k, :]

# Reconstruct the compressed image
compressed_image = U_k @ S_k @ Vt_k

# Display compressed image
plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
plt.imshow(compressed_image, cmap='gray')
plt.title(f"Compressed Image (k={k})")
plt.axis('off')
plt.show()

#  +  k 
from scipy.linalg import svd

# image_array 
U, S, Vt = svd(image_array, full_matrices=False)

ks = [10, 50, 100, 200]  #  k 
fig, axs = plt.subplots(1, len(ks)+1, figsize=(15,5))

# 
axs[0].imshow(image_array, cmap='gray')
axs[0].set_title("Original")
axs[0].axis('off')

# 
for i, k in enumerate(ks):
    Uk = U[:, :k]
    Sk = np.diag(S[:k])
    Vk = Vt[:k, :]
    compressed = Uk @ Sk @ Vk
    axs[i+1].imshow(compressed, cmap='gray')
    axs[i+1].set_title(f"k={k}")
    axs[i+1].axis('off')

plt.suptitle("Original vs Compressed Images with Different k")
plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()

ks = [5, 10, 20, 50, 100, 150, 200]
psnr_values, ssim_values, cr_values = [], [], []

for k in ks:
    U_k = U[:, :k]
    S_k = np.diag(S[:k])
    Vt_k = Vt[:k, :]
    compressed_image = U_k @ S_k @ Vt_k
    
    psnr_values.append(psnr(image_array, compressed_image, data_range=1))
    ssim_values.append(ssim(image_array, compressed_image, data_range=1))
    cr_values.append((k*(m+n+1))/(m*n))

# Plot results
plt.figure(figsize=(10, 5))
plt.plot(ks, psnr_values, marker='o', label='PSNR (dB)')
plt.plot(ks, [cr*100 for cr in cr_values], marker='s', label='Compression Ratio (%)')
plt.title('PSNR and Compression Ratio vs. Rank (k)')
plt.xlabel('Rank (k)')
plt.ylabel('Value')
plt.grid(True)
plt.legend()
plt.show()
